# Reflection Statement

## Key Learnings  
Throughout the Java Task Manager project, I've gained a deeper understanding of object-oriented programming principles, specifically encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism. Additionally, I learned how to effectively manage changes and collaborate in a team environment using Git. The importance of writing clean, maintainable code became evident through code reviews and feedback from peers.

## Improvements  
I identified the need to enhance my debugging skills and became more proficient with tools like JDB. I also realized the importance of better time management during the project phases, which will help in allocating appropriate resources and preventing bottlenecks in future projects.

## Start/Stop/Continue Actions  
- **Start**: Regularly participating in code reviews and seeking feedback to foster continuous learning.  
- **Stop**: Procrastinating, particularly during the planning phase of the project, to avoid rushed deliveries.  
- **Continue**: Using Agile methodologies for project management to adapt quickly to changes and maintain productivity.

## Success Metrics  
- Completed the project on time, satisfying the deadline with an organized set of features implemented.  
- Achieved a code quality score of 90% based on static analysis tools used during the review processes.  
- Positive feedback from peers during the final presentation, reflecting the quality and usability of the application.